data.title: FROM TIME TO TIME
data.meta_description: Time and tide waits for no man. To capture time, treasure every moment in your life and let the time that slowly slips away memorable and worthy to be kept as sweet memories.
data.text:
NEW CABINET LINE-UP TO BE ANNOUNCED EARLY NEXT WEEK , 17TH. OR 18TH. MARCH 2008

It is exactly a week ago when all Malaysian who have registered started to go voting for the 12th. General Election. The results were already announced by last Sunday on 9th. of March 2008.

Keputusan Pilihanraya Yang ke 12 Untuk Parlimen dan DUN(The results of the 12th. General Election for Malaysia FOR Parliament and State)

Parliament (Parlimen):

BN - 140

OPPOSITION - 82 (DAP 28, PKR 31 AND PAS 23)

State (DUN):

BN - 306

OPPOSITION - 195

- as announced on 8pm news , 9th March 2008

Barisan Nasion won 140 of the 222 Parliament seats for the 12th. General Election which took place on 8th. March 2008, Saturday.

Barisan Nasiona lost five states (DUN) to the opposition - Kedah, Penang, Selangor, Perak and Kelantan.

Many people are waiting for the new cabinet line-up to be announced early next week.

WOW! I BOUGHT SO MUCH FOOD FOR BREAKFAST TOMORROW. I WONDER IT WILL TAKE HOW MANY DAYS FOR ME TO FINISH THEM.

Breads go along well with kaya. Spreading some kaya on the bread makes you asking for more than a piece. Bread - RM3.20 and kaya - RM2.30

They don't sell Gardenia or High Five bread here.

Butter cake and cup cakes

This is called cheese butter cake according to the girl from Taka Bakery. RM5.50

Cup cakes at RM2.00 per packet. Quite cheap.

These are the food I bought from Taka Bakery shop just now when I was on the way back after swimming. Looking at them already make me feel hungry again although I just have my dinner.

It is very rare to see Sunset in Kuching these few months

I have not been feeling too well these two days. Eaten too much panadols and that did not really help. I thought hard and finally I made up my dicision to go for a short swim since today is the best weather eversince I came back.

Quickly packed my things I need to take to the pool. Have I forgotten anything? When I reached the pool it was still so sunny. Imagine, in the east if 6pm is still sunny. Usually at this time, the sky is getting darker. Had a short swim at Waterpark Stampark, Stutong.

Anyway if I wanted to spend longer time swimming it would be quite impossible too as there were so many people at the pool. Then I remembered. Oh yes!! it is still a school holiday. After I had a quick shower there, I started my journey to go home. On the way back, I stopped over at Taka Bakery shop and bought a loaf of bread, some cakes and kaya.

Took some snapshots along the way home. Wow!! how I missed sunset scenery. It has been a very long time since I saw the beautiful sunset or some people called sundown. Which one you prefer? Sunset or sundown. Anyway, it comes from the same meaning. Sunset or sundown is when the sun begins to fall below the horizon and later on vanish altogether and cannot be seen anymore.

When I arrived home, the sky was already getting dark and I can't enjoy myself watching the beautiful scenery of sunset. I wish and pray for good weather tomorrow but I just heard on news that it will be a wet weather here tomorrow.

PEMANGKU SULTAN PERAK, RAJA DR. NAZRIN SHAH AND RAJA PUAN BESAR PERAK, TUANKU ZARA SALIM ARE BLESSED WITH A PRINCE AT 10AM ON 14TH MARCH 2008, FRIDAY

It was announced on news over Astro Channel 502 that Pemangku Sultan Perak, Raja Dr. Nazrin Steven Shah and Raja Puan Besar Perak, Tuanku Zara Salim Davidson are blessed with a prince earlier this morning, Friday. The prince was born at the Damansara Specialist Hospital at 10am. Both Raja Puan Besar and the prince are in good health.

- Pemangku Sultan Perak, Raja Dr. Nazrin Steven Shah dan Raja Puan Besar, Tuanku Zara Salim Davidson telah dikurniakan seorang putera pada pukul 10 pagi, Jumaat hari ini. Kedua-dua Raja Puan Besar dan putera mereka berada dalam keadaan sihat -

Some information about Pemangku Sultan Perak, the Crown Prince of Perak:

His full name including official titles: Duli Yang Teramat Mulia Raja Muda Perak Darul Ridzuan Raja Dr. Nazrin Steven Shah Ibni Sultan Azlan Muhibbuddin D.K., D.K.II (Selangor), D.K.S.A, S.P.C.M, S.P.T.S, S.P.M.P. (Perlis), Ph.D (Harvard).

Raja Dr. Nazrin Steven Shah born on 27th. November 1956 in Penang, is eldest son of Sultan of Perak, Sultan Azlan Muhibbudin Shah ibni Almarhum Sultan Yusuff Izzudin Shah Ghafarullahu-lahu and the Raja Permaisuri of Perak Tuanku Bainun Binti Mohd. Ali.

He is the Crown Prince (Duli Yang Teramat Mulia Raja Muda Perak on 15th. April 1984.

Pemangku Sultan Perak, Raja Dr. Nazrin Steven Shah and Raja Puan Besar, Tuanku Zara Salim Davidson got married at Istana Iskandariah, Bukit Chandan, Kuala Kangsar on 17th. May 2007 and the royal wedding reception took place two days later on 19th. May 2007.

On 14th. March 2008, Friday both Pemangku Sultan Perak, Raja Dr. Nazrin Steven Shah and Raja Puan Besar, Tuanku Zara Salim Davidson are blessed with a prince at 10am.

Some information about Puan Raja Besar Perak:

Duli Yang Teramat Mulia Raja Puan Besar Perak, Tuanku Zara Salim Davidson born on 22nd. March 1973 in Ipoh, Perak Darul Ridzuan is the youngest daughter of Salim Davidson, a wel known lawyer in Perak and Sharifah Azaliah Syed Omar Shahabudin. She has three elder brothers.

Tuanku Zara Salim Davidson is the great grand daughter of the former Sultan of Kedah, Sultan Sir Abdul Hamid Halim Shah ibni al-Marhum Sultan Ahmad Tajuddin Mukarram Shah (4th June 1864 to 13th. May 1943). She is also the granddaughter of the former Kedah Menteri Besar, Tan Sri Syed Omar Syed Abdullah Shahabudin and a grandniece of first Prime Minister Tunku Abdul Rahman.

Tuanku Zara Salim Davidson was a state swimmer for Perak from 1981 to 1987 and represented her school in squash and tennis for two years in 1988 to 1990. Other than that, she has a deep interest in foreign languages.

After she completed her A Levels in 1992, she went to United Kingdom, England to further her studies in chemical engineering at NottinghamUniversity and she graduated with a first class honours degree three years later in 1995. Other than than her excellent achievement in chemical engineering, she was also awarded as the top student for her final year project.

She is certified as life-saver and adventure sports enthusiast from the year 2005 to 2007 and she later became Managing Director Of Forthwave Consulting Sdn. Bhd, Kuala Lumpur.

Raja Puan Besar Perak, Tuanku Zara Salim Davidson got married to Pemangku Sultan Perak, Raja Dr. Nazrin Steven Shah on 17th. May 2007. A day after her marriage on May 17, 2007, she is proclaimed Raja Puan Besar Perak at a ceremony in Istana Iskandariah, Bukit Chandan, Kuala Kangsar.

Raja Puan Besar Perak, Tuanku Zara Salim Davidson gave birth to a prince this morning at 10am on 14th. March 2008, Friday. She and the prince are in good health.

We miss you Harry. - You will always be remembered -

Harry left me suddenly on 13th. March 2008 of an unknown reason. He was still healthy when I bathed him and fed him two days ago.

You were taken away from us suddenly and our lives will never be the same again. We know you are in a much better place now with your friends Mindy, Nano, Nana, Nani, Rayar, Aideel, Fitry and Sunny. You are sadly missed more than you could ever know. You will forever be in our hearts.- We miss you from: Owner Sapphire Blu, friends: Mork, N, Da Da, Ka Ka, Ki Ki, Light & Missa -

May Harry Rest In Peace. Departed on 13th March 2008
